%2C%20along%20with%20other%20advice.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWolobah's%20parents%2C%20Amos%20and%20Lois%2C%20told%20WBZ-TV%20that%20their%20son%20had%20fainted%20after%20eating%20the%20chip%20at%20school%2C%20and%20after%20returning%20home%20he%20passed%20out%20a%20second%20time%2C%20and%20later%20died%20in%20the%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWolobah%20had%20no%20known%20allergies%20and%20was%20a%20healthy%20basketball%20player%2C%20they%20told%20the%20outlet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20hope%2C%20I%20pray%20to%20God%20that%20no%20parents%20will%20go%20through%20what%20I'm%20going%20through%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20boy's%20mother%20told%20WBZ-TV.%20%26quot%3BI%20miss%20my%20son%20so%20much.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3BOne%20Chip%20Challenge%26quot%3B%20has%20been%20around%20for%20several%20years%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fcarolina-reaper-madness-chip-spiciest-tortilla-one-challenge-2016-10%5C%22%3Ewas%20reviewed%20by%20Insider's%20video%20team%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20a%20California%20high%20school%20reported%20three%20cases%20of%20students%20needing%20medical%20attention%20after%20taking%20on%20the%20challenge%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fone-chip-challenge-reportedly-prompts-multiple-hospitalizations-2022-1%5C%22%3EInsider's%20Kieran%20Press-Reynolds%20reported%20at%20the%20time%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20challenge%20is%20hugely%20popular%20on%20social%20media%2C%20with%20the%20hashtag%20%23onechipchallenge%20being%20marked%20as%20viewed%20more%20than%20two%20billion%20times%20on%20TikTok.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaqui%2C%20its%20parent%20company%20Amplify%20Snacks%2C%20and%20The%20Hershey%20Company%2C%20which%20owns%20Amplify%2C%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20out-of-hours%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20a%20statement%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%