2Fa%3E.%20But%20the%20program%20has%20long%20come%20under%20fire%20for%20its%20ever-expanding%20budget%20and%20its%20lagging%20deadlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSenior%20agency%20officials%20have%20told%20us%20that%20at%20current%20cost%20levels%20the%20SLS%20program%20is%20unsustainable%20and%20exceeds%20what%20NASA%20officials%20believe%20will%20be%20available%20for%20its%20Artemis%20missions%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fproducts%2Fgao-23-105609%5C%22%3EGovernment%20Accountability%20Office%3C%2Fa%3E%20(GAO)%20said%20in%20a%20report%20published%20Thursday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20exact%20costs%20are%20unclear%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20GAO%20says%20NASA%20has%20spent%20%2411.8%20billion%20since%202011%20on%20the%20development%20of%20the%20integrated%20SLS%20rocket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20a%20wild%20variation%20in%20numbers%20reported%20about%20the%20actual%20cost%20of%20this%20program%2C%20which%20depends%20on%20whether%20the%20development%20of%20the%20Orion%20spaceship%20%E2%80%94%20which%20predates%20SLS%20%E2%80%94%20and%20other%20running%20costs%20are%20included.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20estimate%2C%20drawn%20from%20NASA's%20Congressional%20Budget%20justification%2C%20puts%20that%20number%20at%20about%20%2450%20billion%2C%20when%20including%20costs%20linked%20to%20developing%20the%20Orion%20capsule%20since%202006%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20per%20the%20Planetary%20Society.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20spending%20doesn't%20stop%20here.%20NASA%20has%20requested%20another%20%2411.2%20billion%20for%20the%20next%20five%20years%20to%20further%20improve%20and%20produce%20the%20next%20iterations%20of%20the%20rocket%2C%20per%20the%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFurther%20SLS%20and%20Orion%20improvements%20are%20making%20up%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.planetary.org%2Fspace-policy%2Fnasas-fy-2024-budget%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIt%2520provides%2520%252425.3%2520billion%2520for%2Ca%2520billion%2520relative%2520to%25202023.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubstantial%20chunk%20of%20the%20agency%3C%2Fa%3E's%20relatively%20small%20budget%20%E2%80%94%20about%20a%20seventh%20of%20the%20%2427.2%20billion%20budget%20it%20has%20requested%20in%202024%2C%20per%20the%20Planetary%20Society.%20By%20comparison%2C%20the%20proposed%20defense%20budget%20for%202024%20is%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defense.gov%2FNews%2FReleases%2FRelease%2FArticle%2F3326875%2Fdepartment-of-defense-releases-the-presidents-fiscal-year-2024-defense-budget%2F%5C%22%3E30%20times%20%3C%2Fa%3Elarger.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20in%20stark%20contrast%20to%20private%20companies%20like%20Elon%20Musk's%20SpaceX%2C%20which%20are%20pushing%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-spacex-starship-rocket-update-flight-cost-million-2022-2%5C%22%3Ereduce%20their%20own%20rockets'%20launch%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20officials%20have%20admitted%20their%20spending%20on%20the%20program%20%26quot%3Bneeds%20to%20be%20improved%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20is%20not%20yet%20clear%20how%20they%20aim%20to%20achieve%20this%2C%20per%20the%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESLS%20is%20NASA's%20workhorse%20for%20lunar%20missions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rocket%20is%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-spacex-starship-launch-crucial-nasa-moon-return-sls-2023-3%5C%22%3Ecenter%20of%20NASA's%20moon%20strategy%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20upcoming%20Artemis%20mission%20because%20it%20is%20the%20only%20rocket%20that's%20built%20to%20fit%20within%20those%20missions%2C%20Brendan%20Rosseau%2C%20a%20teaching%20fellow%20of%20space%20economy%20at%20Harvard%20Business%20School%2C%20previously%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20NASA%20has%20planned%20a%20series%20of%20missions%20that%20will%20put%20boots%20on%20the%20moon%20at%20first%2C%20before%20aiming%20to%20establish%20a%20lunar%20base.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223804%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22NASA's%20SLS%20rocket%20is%20shown%20being%20rolled%20out%20of%20an%20assembly%20hanger.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64fae544a39a1b00190b7db5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221902%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENASA's%20SLS%20rocket%20and%20Orion%20spacecraft%20shown%20here%20being%20rolled%20of%20their%20assembly%20building%20ahead%20of%20the%20Artemis%20I%20mission.%20After%20the%20succesfull%20mission%2C%20NASA%20has%20admitted%20the%20mega-rocket's%20growing%20budget%20is%20%26quot%3Bunsustainable%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20a%20government%20report%20release%20Sept%208%2C%202023.%3Cp%3ENASA%2FJoel%20Kowsky%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plan%20is%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-nasa-sls-moon-rocket-taller-than-statue-of-liberty-2021-10%5C%22%3ESLS%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20carry%20people%20to%20the%20orbit%20of%20the%20moon%2C%20where%20it%20will%20meet%20up%20with%20a%20lunar%20lander%20that%20can%20pick%20up%20astronauts%20and%20bring%20them%20down%20to%20the%20lunar%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENASA's%20people%20carrier%2C%20the%20Orion%20spacecraft%2C%20is%20at%20the%20center%20of%20these%20missions.%20And%20it%20was%20specifically%20designed%20to%20fit%20with%20the%20SLS%20booster%2C%20and%20not%20another%20rocket%2C%20per%20Rosseau%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNASA's%20worked%20really%20hard%20on%20it.%20It%20seems%20like%20they're%20going%20to%20stick%20with%20this%20for%20a%20while%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosseau%20previously%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENASA's%20SLS%20is%20an%20anomaly%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20criticism%20for%20the%20SLS%20program%20is%20that%20it%20sticks%20out%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bbit%20of%20an%20anomaly%26quot%3B%20in%20NASA's%20latest%20approach%20to%20project%20development%2C%20Rosseau%20previously%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDriven%20by%20a%20political%20will%20to%20bring%20down%20the%20cost%20of%20space%20exploration%2C%20NASA%20has%20been%20moving%20away%20from%20developing%20its%20tech%20in-house%20over%20the%20past%20few%20decades%2C%20instead%20preferring%20to%20issue%20one-time%20contracts%20to%20commercial%20providers%20who%20can%20deliver%20a%20service%20for%20a%20set%20price.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20move%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-helping-private-companies-build-business-moon-make-lunar-billions-2023-6%5C%22%3Ecommercial-first%20mindset%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20crucial%20to%20the%20development%20of%20the%20private%20space%20industry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20led%20to%20stiff%20competition%2C%20with%20SpaceX%20moving%20forward%20with%20the%20development%20of%20its%20own%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarship-spacex-elon-musk-reusable-rocket-mars-moon-launch-2023-2%5C%22%3EStarship%20mega-rocket%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20after%20it%20landed%20a%20%242.9%20billion%20contract%20to%20create%20a%20lunar%20lander%20for%20NASA's%20Artemis%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20also%20recently%20awarded%20a%20%243.4%20billion%20contract%20to%20Blue%20Origin%20to%20develop%20a%20lunar%20lander%20for%20another%20Artemis%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Starship%20black%20rocket%20lifts%20off%20from%20texas%20plains%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64faf93fa39a1b00190b8a7d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStarship%20launches%20toward%20orbit%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3Cp%3ESpaceX%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20price%20tag%20and%20how%20long%20it's%20taken%20to%20develop%20and%20the%20problems%20that%20it's%20had%2C%20maybe%20it's%20evidence%20that%20buying%20services%20from%20the%20commercial%20sector%20really%20is%20the%20way%20to%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosseau%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20have%20been%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fspacenews.com%2Fwhat-future-for-the-space-launch-system%2F%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%228924695174c738001f2e24b976e79a3d%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2280%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fspacenews.com%2Fwhat-future-for-the-space-launch-system%2F%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epolitical%20gambit%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20rather%20than%20a%20business%20decision%2C%20that%20drove%20SLS's%20continued%20investment%2C%20Rosseau%20previously%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20cynics%20would%20say%20that%20it%20was%20congressional%20appropriators%20and%20senators%20with%20parochial%20interests%20who%20really%20wanted%20NASA%20to%20be%20building%20a%20giant%20rocket%20just%20for%20the%20jobs%20in%20their%20districts%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20SLS%20is%20the%20only%20rocket%20of%20that%20power%20class%20that%20has%20demonstrated%20that%20it%20can%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20attempted%20its%20first%20fully%20stacked%20launch%20of%20Starship%20in%20April%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-spacex-starship-rocket-explodes-first-orbital-launch-attempt-2023-4%5C%22%3Eended%20in%20a%20fireball%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20the%20spacecraft%20failed%20to%20separate%20from%20its%20booster%20while%20in%20flight.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Picture%20shows%20a%20fireball%20in%20the%20sky%20caused%20by%20the%20explosion%20of%20SpaceX's%20Starship%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e3631abd98a600197ac7a4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESpaceX's%20Starship%20exploded%20this%20morning%20on%20its%20first%20launch%2C%20causing%20a%20huge%20fireball%20in%20the%20sky.%3Cp%3ESpaceX%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3ENASA%20is%20working%20to%20bring%20costs%20under%20control%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20clear%20how%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENASA%20has%20said%20it%20is%20now%20aiming%20to%20pare%20back%20its%20costs%20using%20a%20four-point%20strategy%3A%20%26quot%3B(1)%20stabilize%20the%20flight%20schedule%2C%20(2)%20achieve%20learning%20curve%20efficiencies%2C%20(3)%20encourage%20innovation%2C%20and%20(4)%20adjust%20acquisition%20strategies%20to%20reduce%20cost%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20states.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20per%20the%20report%2C%20NASA%20%26quot%3Bhas%20not%20yet%20identified%20specific%20program-level%20cost-saving%20goals%20which%20it%20hopes%20to%20achieve.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20said%20moves%20have%20been%20made%20to%20reach%20those%20goals%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20clear%20whether%20they've%20led%20to%20savings%20so%20far%2C%20per%20the%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farstechnica.com%2Fspace%2F2023%2F09%2Fnasa-finally-admits-what-everyone-already-knows-sls-is-unaffordable%2F%5C%22%3Ereason%20to%20question%3C%2Fa%3E%20whether%20NASA%20can%20achieve%20its%20cost-saving%20goals%2C%20Ars%20Technica%20senior%20space%20editor%20Eric%20Berger%20wrote%20Thursday.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20plan%20from%20NASA%20to%20reduce%20the%20cost%20of%20SLS's%20rocket%20engines%20by%2030%25%20down%20to%20%2470.5%20million%20has%20been%20criticized%20by%20NASA's%20general%20inspector%2C%20Paul%20Martin%2C%20who%20said%20the%20budget%20did%20not%20include%20project%20management%20and%20overhead%20costs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20engines%20would%20still%20also%20be%20far%20more%20expensive%20than%20equivalent%20private%20engines%2C%20per%20Berger.%20Blue%20Origin's%20BE-4%20engines%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20are%20manufactured%20for%20less%20than%20%2420%20million%2C%20and%20SpaceX%20wants%20to%20bring%20its%20Raptor%20to%20a%20cost%20under%20%241%20milli