023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694172753000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d66893f3f87e001951ddb2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-cybertruck-mcdonalds-elon-musk-china-promotion-fake-news-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Details%20about%20the%20limited-edition%20McFlurry%20spoons%20came%20from%20Tesla's%20verified%20Weibo%20page.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bnolan%40insider.com%20(Beatrice%20Nolan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-cybertruck-mcdonalds-elon-musk-china-promotion-fake-news-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Vishwaguru%20and%20the%20Crisis%20of%20Democracy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F12114331%2F33F81A3F-BCF6-4D05-975C-264958F029F4_1_105_c.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20August%20survey%20by%20the%20reputed%20Pew%20Research%20Center%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fpew-research-finds-indians-more-confident-of-country-than-rest-of-world%5C%22%3E68%25%20of%20Indians%20say%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20global%20influence%20has%20gotten%20stronger.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flokniti.org%2Fmedia%2Fupload_files%2FSocial-and-Political-Barometer-2023-Survey-findings.pdf%5C%22%3E2023%20Lokniti-CSDS%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2054%25%20(and%2071%25%20of%20those%20with%20high%20media%20exposure)%20believed%20that%20India%20has%20emerged%20as%20the%20Vishwaguru%C2%A0under%20the%20leadership%20of%20Narendra%20Modi.%20According%20to%20Pew%2C%2079%25%20of%20Indians%20have%20a%20favourable%20view%20of%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpinion%20surveys%20do%20not%20tell%20us%20the%20complete%20reality%2C%20but%20are%20an%20important%20statistical%20tool%20to%20understand%20large%20social%20trends.%20Why%20are%20these%20facts%2C%20therefore%2C%20noteworthy%3F%20Because%20they%20do%20not%20match%20with%20foreign%20assessments%20about%20the%20world%20standing%20of%20India%2C%20or%20that%20of%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20according%20to%20Pew%2C%20only%20a%2028%25%20median%20(19%20countries)%20said%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20influence%20has%20grown%20stronger.%20While%20a%2046%25%20median%20(23%20countries)%20had%20a%20favourable%20opinion%20of%20India%20(against%2034%25%20unfavourability%20rating)%2C%20in%20many%20of%20these%20countries%2C%20especially%20in%20Europe%2C%20the%20favourability%20of%20India%20was%20substantially%20higher%20in%20earlier%20surveys%20in%202008%2F2013.%20And%2C%20unlike%20domestic%20opinion%20and%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20relentless%20propagation%20of%20the%20idea%20that%20Modi%20is%20a%20popular%20global%20leader%20leading%20the%20world%2C%20only%2037%25%20median%20in%2012%20countries%20have%20confidence%20in%20him%20against%2040%25%20who%20have%20no%20confidence.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20where%2051%25%20people%20favour%20India%2C%20the%20confidence%20in%20Modi%20is%2021%25%2C%20while%20in%20Israel%2C%20where%2071%25%20favours%20India%2C%20the%20confidence%20in%20him%20is%2041%25%20demonstrating%20huge%20gaps.%20As%20much%20as%2040%25%20of%20Americans%20(and%2059%25%20in%20the%2018-29%20age%20category)%20have%20never%20heard%20of%20Modi%20(the%20lowest%20percentage%20amongst%20the%20leaders%20in%20the%20survey%3A%20Zelenskyy%2C%20Macron%2C%20Scholz%2C%20Netanyahu%2C%20Modi%2C%20Xi%20and%20Putin).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20staggering%20difference%20between%20domestic%20and%20foreign%20evaluation%2C%20and%20the%20substantial%20domestic%20acceptance%2C%20even%20across%20partisan%20lines%2C%20of%20the%20belief%20that%20India%20is%20already%20a%20Vishwaguru%2C%20are%20significant%20for%20two%20things%3A%20first%2C%20the%20success%20of%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20government%20in%20making%20their%20version%20of%20nationalism%20almost%20ironclad%2C%20and%20second%2C%20the%20relevance%20of%20the%20concept%20of%20post-truth.%20Post-truth%2C%20as%20scholars%20describe%20it%2C%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9Cerosion%20of%20simple%20factual%20truths%2C%20truths%20that%20technically%20anyone%20could%20verify%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20systematic%20use%20of%20blatant%20lies%E2%80%9D.%20While%20lies%20always%20existed%20in%20history%2C%20under%20post-truth%2C%20truth%20itself%20becomes%20immaterial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Will%20India's%20'Development'%20Move%20Past%20Bombast%20and%20Pretending%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwill-indias-development-move-past-bombast-and-pretending%5C%22%3EWill%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Development%E2%80%99%20Move%20Past%20Bombast%20and%20Pretending%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20while%20the%20official%20discourse%20is%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20reputation%20has%20increased%20phenomenally%20under%20Modi%2C%20and%20the%20tagline%20for%20G20%20is%20India%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9CMother%20of%20Democracy%2C%E2%80%9D%20in%20Kafkaesque%20irony%2C%20India%20has%20suffered%20the%20greatest%20loss%20of%20global%20reputation%20since%20the%20Emergency%20of%201975%20precisely%20because%20of%20severe%20democracy%20erosion%20and%20religious%20majoritarianism%20in%20the%20last%20nine%20years.%20This%20has%20been%20subject%20to%20widespread%2C%20global%20condemnation%20and%20criticism%2C%20as%20documented%20by%20the%20responses%20from%20foreign%20media%20and%20academia%2C%20human%20rights%20and%20democracy%20reports%20and%20rankings%20by%20organisations%20like%20the%20Varieties%20of%20Democracy%20Institute%2C%20Freedom%20House%2C%20Economist%20Intelligence%20Unit%2C%20Amnesty%20International%2C%20Human%20Rights%20Watch%20and%20Reporters%20without%20Borders%2C%20to%20name%20only%20a%20few%2C%20and%20even%20responses%20from%20governments%20and%20legislatures%20in%20the%20West%2C%20and%20Gulf%20countries%2C%20etc.%2C%20who%20otherwise%20practice%20only%20realpolitik.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20under%20post-truth%2C%20this%20%E2%80%9Creality%E2%80%9D%20of%20criticisms%20does%20not%20make%20any%20difference%20to%20the%20domestic%20self-assessment%20of%20India%20as%20a%20Vishwaguru%2C%20or%20ironically%2C%20even%20strengthens%20it.%20While%20the%20government%20and%20its%20supporters%20have%2C%20rightly%2C%20questioned%20the%20hypocrisy%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccolonialist%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cimperialist%E2%80%9D%20Western%20governments%20in%20criticising%20the%20democracy%20record%20of%20other%20countries%2C%20they%20have%20also%2C%20wrongly%2C%20painted%20all%20foreign%20criticisms%20as%20a%20part%20of%20grand%20conspiracy%20against%20a%20rising%20India%2C%20and%20Hindu%20civilisation.%20Here%2C%20the%20domination%20of%20the%20idea%20of%20nationalism%20draws%20in%20even%20those%20who%20are%20not%20narrowly%20identified%20with%20Hindutva.%20Like%20many%20other%20majoritarian%20ethnic%20projects%20elsewhere%2C%20the%20populist%2C%20Hindu%20nationalist%20project%20of%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20the%20BJP%20and%20have%20managed%20to%20build%20an%20immunity%20which%20disqualifies%20even%20domestic%20critics%20as%20anti-national.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20foreign%20governments%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20West%2C%20have%20lent%20credence%20to%20the%20Vishwaguru%20narrative%20by%20increasing%20strategic%20and%20economic%20cooperation%20with%20India%20and%20with%20acts%20like%20their%20leaders%20appearing%20together%20with%20Modi%20in%20Indian%20diaspora%20rallies%2C%20duly%20marketed%20breathlessly%20by%20the%20mainstream%20media%20for%20a%20domestic%20audience.%20But%20the%20fundamental%20animator%20of%20the%20changed%20geopolitical%20scenario%20in%20which%20India%20becomes%20more%20important%20is%20China%20and%20the%20necessity%20for%20a%20bulwark%20against%20it%20(in%20contrast%20to%20India%2C%20in%202019%2C%20a%20median%20of%2070%25%20in%2025%20countries%20said%20China%20played%20a%20bigger%20role%20in%20the%20world%20compared%20to%20a%20decade%20before%20%E2%80%93%20Pew%202019).%20Besides%2C%20there%20are%20factors%20like%20the%20demographic%20size%20of%20India%2C%20its%20inevitable%20economic%20rise%2C%20its%20democratic%20legacy%2C%20and%20the%20power%20of%20a%20large%20diaspora%2C%20which%20make%20the%20world%20increasingly%20engage%20with%20India%2C%20irrespective%20of%20the%20ruling%20party%20(as%20early%20as%202010%2C%20President%20Obama%20had%20said%20that%20India%20is%20not%20emerging%2C%20but%20%E2%80%9Chas%20already%20risen%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20power).%20Yet%2C%20the%20Hindu%20nationalist%20project%20has%20successfully%20made%20these%20factors%20seem%20like%20Modi%20government%20achievements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20country%20after%20India%20which%20has%20the%20most%20inflated%20opinion%20about%20its%20power%20is%20Russia%2C%20with%20a%2030%25%20difference%20between%20self-evaluation%20and%20foreign%20assessment%20(Pew%202018).%20And%20we%20have%20seen%20the%20kind%20of%20depredations%20its%20great%20power%20ambitions%20have%20wrought%20on%20its%20own%20people%20and%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22'They%20Really%20Descend%20on%20Journalism%20They%20Don't%20Like'%3A%20Press%20Freedom%20in%20India%2C%20on%20the%20Eve%20of%20the%20G20%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fm20-india-press-freedom-g20-impunity-it-cell%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98They%20Really%20Descend%20on%20Journalism%20They%20Don%E2%80%99t%20Like%E2%80%99%3A%20Press%20Freedom%20in%20India%2C%20on%20the%20Eve%20of%20the%20G20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20a%20political%20discourse%20centred%20around%20Vishwaguru%20is%20deeply%20scarring%20for%20democracy.%20Not%20only%20does%20it%20hide%20the%20democratic%20backsliding%20in%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20democracy%2C%20but%20also%20deflects%20attention%20from%20the%20fundamental%20problems%20in%20a%20country%20with%20a%20nominal%20per%20capita%20GDP%20of%20%242%2C388%20(ranked%20139%20out%20of%20192%20countries)%20and%20the%20largest%20global%20population%20of%20poor%20(230%20million%20people%2C%20almost%20equivalent%20to%20the%20fifth%20most%20populous%20country%20in%20the%20world).%20While%2060%25%20surveyed%20in%202023%20believe%20that%20their%20incomes%20do%20not%20meet%20basic%20needs%2C%2042%25%20feel%20that%20nothing%20has%20changed%20and%2022%25%20feel%20that%20conditions%20have%20deteriorated%2C%20astonishingly%2C%2047%25%20of%20poor%20believe%20that%20India%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20Vishwaguru%20(Lokniti-CSDS%202023)%20demonstrating%20how%20post-truth%20communications%20have%20penetrated%20even%20the%20most%20vulnerable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20propaganda%2C%20fake%20news%20and%20a%20near%20domination%20of%20the%20mainstream%20media%20have%20aided%20Hindu%20nationalism%20and%20its%20Vishwaguru%20claims%20(for%20example%3A%20the%20government%20assertions%20on%20COVID-19%20vaccination%20and%20the%20Russo-Ukraine%20War).%20But%20post-truth%20in%20general%2C%20or%20specifically%20regarding%20Vishwaguru%2C%20which%20is%20also%20based%20on%20religious%20and%20civilisational%20supremacy%2C%20cannot%20be%20countered%20by%20facts%20alone.%20Facts%20cannot%20survive%20without%20socio-political%20structures%20supporting%20them.%20What%20has%20led%20to%20the%20domination%20of%20Hindu%20nationalism%20is%20the%20collapse%20of%20trust%20in%20%E2%80%9Csecularist%E2%80%9D%20politics%2C%20making%20the%20former%E2%80%99s%20claims%20less%20about%20facts%20and%20the%20truth%2C%20and%20more%20about%20who%20is%20making%20the%20claim.%20While%20Hindutva%20has%20been%20defeated%20electorally%20at%20the%20state%20level%2C%20a%20political%20imagination%20that%20can%20challenge%20its%20nationalist%20project%20and%20propose%20a%20new%2C%20inclusive%20and%20modest%20nationalism%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20identified.%20Remember%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20used%20the%20shield%20of%20a%20muscular%20nationalism%20to%20easily%20weather%20crises%20like%20demonetisation%2C%20COVID-19%20excess%20deaths%2C%20Chinese%20aggression%20at%20the%20border%20for%20three%20years%2C%20and%20alleged%20Adani%20stock%20manipulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20can%20be%20attempted%20in%20the%20meantime%20is%20the%20delineation%20of%20the%20ill%20effects%20on%20democracy%20of%20a%20lower%20middle-income%20country%2C%20with%20a%20human%20development%20rank%20of%20132%2C%20in%20the%20thralldom%20of%20being%20a%20Vishwaguru.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENissim%20Mannathukkaren%20is%20Professor%2C%20International%20Development%20Studies%2C%20Dalhousie%20University%2C%20Canada.%20He%20tweets%20%40nmannathukkaren.%20Some%20of%20the%20arguments%20here%20and%20supporting%20data%20are%20elaborated%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1080%2F01436597.2023.2231890%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20co-authored%20with%20Drew%20MacEachern%20recently%20in%20the%20Third%20World%20Quarterly%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694172487000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fvishwaguru-and-the-crisis-of-democracy%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20political%20discourse%20centred%20around%20Vishwaguru%20is%20deeply%20scarring%20for%20democracy.%20Not%20only%20does%20it%20hide%20the%20democratic%20backsliding%20in%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20democracy%2C%20but%20also%20deflects%20attention%20from%20the%20fundamental%20problems%20in%20the%20country.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fvishwaguru-and-the-crisis-of-democracy%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Insider%20Today%3A%20Analyzing%20Google%20salaries%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227332%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sundar%20Pichai%2C%20CEO%20of%20Google%2C%20wears%20a%20gray%20swea