%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b88ac08a4e660019e3c0ed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20army's%2035th%20Marine%20Brigade%20members%20conduct%20mine%20clearance%20work%20at%20a%20field%20in%20Donetsk%2C%20Ukraine%20on%20July%2011%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EErcin%20Erturk%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERussia%20began%20laying%20minefields%20deeper%20than%20normal%20to%20make%20them%20harder%20for%20Ukraine%20to%20cross.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThey%20didn't%20have%20enough%20land%20mines%20to%20do%20the%20same%20size%2C%20shape%2C%20and%20density%20everywhere%20though%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20report.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThis%20issue%20resulted%20in%20irregular%20and%20inconsistent%20minefields%20that%20still%20have%20created%20headaches%20for%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20it%20constructed%20its%20formidable%20defenses%2C%20Russia%20attempted%20to%20make%20its%20minefields%20deeper%20and%20harder%20for%20Ukrainian%20forces%20to%20cross%20but%20couldn't%20get%20enough%20mines%20to%20fully%20execute%20the%20plan%20everywhere.%20The%20inconsistent%20and%20often%20improvised%20approach%20that%20followed%2C%20however%2C%20still%20created%20headaches%20for%20advancing%20Ukrainian%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.rusi.org%2FStormbreak-Special-Report-web-final_0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Royal%20United%20Service%20Institute%20land%20warfare%20experts%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rusi.org%2Fpeople%2Fjack-watling%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJack%20Watling%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rusi.org%2Fpeople%2Freynolds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENick%20Reynolds%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Ukraine's%20fight%20details%20Russian%20adaptations%20during%20the%20ongoing%20counteroffensive%2C%20and%20irregular%20minefields%20are%20identified%20as%20particularly%20challenging%20aspects%20of%20the%20Russian%20defensive%20strategy%20that%20demand%20not%20only%20more%20equipment%20but%20also%20innovative%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20standard%20Russian%20minefield%20is%20roughly%20120%20meters%20deep%2C%20but%20Russian%20forces%20found%20that%20Ukraine%20could%20breach%20these%20minefields%20with%20equipment%20like%20the%20Soviet-era%20UR-77%20Meteorit%20mine-clearing%20vehicle%20or%20the%20US-provided%20M58%20Mine%20Clearing%20Line%20Charge%20(MICLIC)%20that%20blasts%20a%20narrow%20lane%20through%20mines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20Russia%20moved%20to%20extend%20the%20depth%20of%20the%20minefields%20to%20500%20meters%2C%20%26quot%3Bwell%20beyond%20any%20rapid%20breaching%20capability%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20new%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20logistics%20standpoint%2C%20this%20plan%20created%20a%20problem%2C%20as%20Russian%20brigades%20were%20equipped%20to%20put%20down%20minefields%20in%20a%20manner%20consistent%20with%20the%20country's%20warfighting%20doctrine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20increased%20depth%20of%20the%20fields%20means%20that%20Russian%20forces%20have%20had%20insufficient%20mines%20to%20consistently%20meet%20this%20lay%20down%20with%20a%20density%20of%20mines%20consistent%20with%20doctrine%2C%26quot%3B%20Watling%20and%20Reynolds%20wrote.%20Essentially%2C%20the%20minefields%20got%20bigger%20but%20so%20did%20the%20space%20between%20the%20mines.%20In%20other%20cases%2C%20Russian%20engineers%20simply%20did%20what%20they%20could%20to%20try%20to%20bog%20down%20Ukraine's%20assault%20forces%20as%20long%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20result%20was%20that%20Russian%20minefields%20became%20irregular%2C%20which%20isn't%20necessarily%20out%20of%20the%20ordinary%20to%20begin%20with%20given%20terrain%20and%20time%20considerations.%20They%20varied%20in%20size%20and%20shape%2C%20and%20they%20consisted%20of%20improvised%20mine%20configurations%20that%20sometimes%20emphasized%20lethality%20over%20depth%20and%20density.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20the%20Russian%20ground%20forces%20and%20combat%20engineers%20tasked%20with%20blunting%20the%20much-anticipated%20Ukrainian%20counteroffensive%20sometimes%20put%20two%20anti-tank%20%26quot%3Bmines%20together%20%E2%80%93%20one%20atop%20the%20other%20%E2%80%93%20compensating%20for%20reduced%20density%20by%20ensuring%20that%20vehicles%20are%20immobilised%20by%20single%20mine-strikes%2C%26quot%3B%20even%20those%20assets%20%26quot%3Bequipped%20with%20dozer%20blades.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20particular%20Russian%20improvisation%20is%20one%20Michael%20Kofman%2C%20a%20Russia%20expert%2C%20also%20noted%20after%20a%20recent%20trip%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20explaining%20in%20a%20podcast%20that%20Russia%20is%20%26quot%3Bdoubling%2C%20tripling%20them%20up.%26quot%3B%20Citing%20conversations%20with%20Ukrainian%20forces%2C%20he%20also%20revealed%20that%20Russia%20sometimes%20built%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-built-fake-explosive-trench-traps-to-lure-ukrainian-troops-2023-7%5C%22%3Efake%20trench%20traps%3C%2Fa%3E%20rigged%20with%20explosives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20the%20Russians%20were%20unable%20to%20consistently%20carry%20out%20their%20plan%20for%20deeper%20minefields%20with%20standard%20density%20as%20intended%20due%20to%20the%20insufficient%20supply%20of%20mines%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20result%20has%20been%20improvisation%20of%20explosive%20devices%2C%20the%20diversification%20of%20the%20range%20of%20mines%20ceded%2C%20and%20the%20decreasing%20regularity%20of%20minefields%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20RUSI%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20this%20has%20caused%20problems%20for%20the%20Ukrainians%2C%20the%20authors%20said%2C%20writing%20that%20%26quot%3Balthough%20the%20consistency%20of%20the%20minefields%20is%20now%20diminished%2C%20this%20has%20significantly%20complicated%20Ukrainian%20planning%20and%20minefield%20reconnaissance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukrainian%20army's%2035th%20Marine%20Brigade%20members%20conduct%20mine%20clearance%20work%20at%20a%20field%20in%20Donetsk%2C%20Ukraine%20on%20July%2011%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ca625cce69770019844688%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221901%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20army's%2035th%20Marine%20Brigade%20members%20conduct%20mine%20clearance%20work%20at%20a%20field%20in%20Donetsk%2C%20Ukraine%20on%20July%2011%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-special-forces-engineer-says-russian-land-mines-are-exhausting-2023-7%5C%22%3ERussian%20minefields%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20specifically%20those%20covered%20by%20indirect%20fire%20assets%20like%20mortars%20and%20artillery%20or%20aviation%20elements%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-aviation-helicopters-cause-headaches-for-ukraine-armored-assaults-counteroffensive-2023-6%5C%22%3Eattack%20helicopters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20been%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraines-biggest-threat-russian-minefields-airpower-us-general-2023-7%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBiggest%2520threat%2520to%2520Ukraine%2520in%2Cairpower%252C%2520top%2520US%2520general%2520says%26amp%3Btext%3DUkraine%2527s%2520ongoing%2520counteroffensive%2520is%2520facing%2520stiff%2520Russian%2520resistance%2520and%2520tough%2520defensive%2520fortifications.%5C%22%3Econstant%20challenge%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20Ukraine%20throughout%20its%20counteroffensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20inconsistency%20and%20irregularity%20of%20the%20Russian%20minefields%20has%20only%20further%20complicated%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresently%2C%20%26quot%3BUkrainian%20operations%20are%20inherently%20limited%20