%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Politics%20Came%20Full%20Circle%20in%20the%20Maldives%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F08133506%2Fimage-2021-12-08T133456.641.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20years%20is%20a%20long%20time%20in%20politics%20anywhere%2C%20but%20in%20the%20Maldives%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20enough%20for%20everything%20to%20come%20full%20circle%2C%20with%20time%20spare%20for%20another%20few%20spins%20around%20the%20island%2C%20making%20it%20hard%20to%20distinguish%20true%20progress%20from%20simply%20going%20round%20in%20circles.%20Within%20a%20year%20of%20taking%20office%2C%20President%20Solih%E2%80%99s%20government%20had%20used%20its%20Majlis%20supermajority%20to%20complete%20an%20unprecedented%20overhaul%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20which%20Judge%20Kriegler%20described%2C%20in%20a%20final%20withering%20assessment%2C%20as%20%E2%80%98a%20major%20threat%20to%20democratic%20rule%E2%80%99.%20The%20JSC%20documented%20seventeen%20instances%20in%20which%20the%20court%20had%20violated%20the%20Constitution%20since%202008%2C%20resulting%20in%20five%20sitting%20members%20being%20replaced%20and%20two%20restored.%20The%20bench%20even%20broke%20new%20ground%20by%20including%20its%20first%20female%20judges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReturning%20to%20a%20well-trodden%20path%2C%20in%20November%202019%2C%20former%20Raees%20Yameen%20was%20jailed%2C%20receiving%20a%20five-year%20prison%20sentence%20and%20a%20%245%20million%20fine%20for%20money-laundering%20offences.%20His%20reprieve%20soon%20came%20around%2C%20however%2C%20and%20two%20years%20later%20the%20sentence%20was%20annulled%20on%20a%20technicality.%20After%20being%20named%20as%20the%20PPM%E2%80%99s%20candidate%20for%20the%202023%20elections%2C%20Yameen%20was%20imprisoned%20yet%20again%20in%20December%202022%20on%20bribery%20and%20laundering%20charges%2C%20this%20time%20for%20eleven%20years%20with%20a%20further%20%245%20million%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20288px)%2085vw%2C%20288px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F08144324%2F81UQ8qli34L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22288%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F08144324%2F81UQ8qli34L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%20633w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F08144324%2F81UQ8qli34L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-190x300.jpg%20190w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-672116%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22455%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDaniel%20Bosley%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EDescent%20into%20Paradise%3A%20A%20Journalist%E2%80%99s%20Memoir%20of%20the%20Untold%20Maldives%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EPan%20Macmillan%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20former%20president%20remains%20defiant%2C%20his%20former%20partner%20in%20vice%20Adeeb%20expressed%20remorse%20for%20his%20crimes%20and%20apologized%20to%20the%20Maldivian%20people.%20His%20original%20sentence%2C%20absolved%20following%20the%202018%20election%2C%20was%20re-investigated%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20twenty-year%20prison%20term%20for%20laundering%20and%20embezzlement.%20This%20was%20after%20he%20also%20attempted%20to%20flee%20the%20country%20on%20a%20tugboat%20and%20was%20caught%20by%20the%20Indian%20Intelligence%20Bureau%20in%20Tuticorin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Maldives%E2%80%99%20sad%20spiral%20into%20violence%20continued.%20On%206%20May%202021%2C%20as%20Nasheed%20walked%20from%20Kenereege%20to%20a%20waiting%20car%2C%20an%20explosive%20device%20attached%20to%20a%20parked%20saikal%20detonated%2C%20leaving%20him%20with%20life-threatening%20injuries.%20He%20underwent%20sixteen%20hours%20of%20surgery%20to%20remove%20shrapnel%20that%20had%20shattered%20bones%2C%20perforated%20organs%20and%20lodged%20within%20an%20inch%20of%20his%20heart.%20The%20invincibly%20stubborn%20Anni%20was%20flown%20to%20Europe%20to%20recover%2C%20returning%20to%20take%20up%20his%20chair%20in%20the%20Majlis%20just%20five%20months%20later.%20A%20twenty-six-year-old%20Islamic%20State%20sympathizer%20named%20Adhuham%20Ahmed%20Rasheed%20was%20arrested%20and%20sentenced%20to%20twenty-three%20years%2C%20with%20six%20more%20suspects%20on%20trial%20at%20the%20time%20of%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEighteen%20months%20earlier%2C%20the%20new%20police%20commissioner%2C%20Mohamed%20Hameed%2C%20had%20revealed%20that%20the%20police%20knew%20of%20at%20least%201%2C400%20extremists%20in%20the%20country%20who%20%E2%80%98would%20not%20hesitate%20to%20take%20the%20life%20of%20the%20person%20next%20to%20them%E2%80%99.%20He%20reported%20that%20173%20Maldivians%20had%20crossed%20into%20Syria%2C%20with%20almost%20sixty%20in%20the%20country%20at%20that%20time.%20In%20an%20alarming%20first%2C%20three%20tourists%20were%20stabbed%20(none%20fatally)%20in%20an%20attack%20in%20Hulhumal%C3%A9%20in%20early%202020%2C%20which%20was%20also%20claimed%20by%20the%20Islamic%20State.%20The%20government%20has%20thwarted%20a%20number%20of%20further%20attacks%20and%20arrested%20Mohamed%20Ameen%2C%20an%20Islamic%20State%20recruiter%2C%20who%20was%20also%20being%20pursued%20by%20US%20authorities.%20In%20August%202023%2C%20the%20US%20treasury%20also%20placed%20sanctions%20on%20twenty%20Maldivians%20it%20considered%20to%20be%20al-Qaeda%20or%20ISIS%20operatives%2C%20including%20Aalif%20Rauf%2C%20alleging%20that%20he%20and%20his%20brothers%20used%20Kuda%20Henveiru%20for%20fundraising%20and%20recruitment.%20Concerns%20persist%2C%20however%2C%20over%20the%20apparent%20inability%20to%20root%20out%20these%20malicious%20networks.%20Their%20political%20influence%20was%20demonstrated%20when%20the%20Maldivian%20Democracy%20Network%20was%20banned%20on%20charges%20of%20blasphemy%20in%20late%202019%2C%20after%20conservatives%20took%20issue%20with%20its%20fouryear-old%20report%20on%20radicalization.%20Demonstrations%20across%20the%20country%20called%20for%20the%20authors%20to%20be%20executed%2C%20as%20the%20Adhaalath-dominated%20Islamic%20ministry%20declared%20them%20apostates%20who%20deserved%20the%20death%20penalty%20and%20forced%20them%20into%20exile%2C%20where%20they%20remain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20in%202021%20to%20criminalize%20just%20this%20kind%20of%20takfiri%20rhetoric%20as%20hate%20speech%2C%20including%20the%20use%20of%20the%20term%20laadheenee%2C%20met%20ferocious%20opposition%2C%20with%20conservative%20networks%20labelling%20it%20the%20%E2%80%98Secular%20Bill%E2%80%99.%20The%20MP%20who%20presented%20it%20was%20bombarded%20with%20death%20threats%2C%20and%20the%20bill%20was%20watered%20down.%20DDCom%20announced%20on%20the%20seventh%20anniversary%20of%20Riz%E2%80%99s%20disappearance%20that%20they%20had%20started%20work%20on%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20first%20witness%20protection%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20murder%20trial%20of%20Yameen%20Rasheed%2C%20after%20agonizingly%20slow%20progress%2C%20life%20sentences%20were%20handed%20to%20two%20men%20in%20early%202022%3A%20twenty-one-year-old%20Ismail%20Haisham%20Rasheed%20and%20twenty-two-year-old%20Ahmed%20Zihan%20Ismail.%20Four%20more%20were%20acquitted%2C%20and%20the%20family%20continues%20to%20press%20for%20the%20ringleaders%20to%20be%20brought%20to%20justice.%20In%20Riz%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20more%20foreign%20investigators%20were%20eventually%20brought%20in%2C%20and%20three%20men%20were%20arrested%20in%20July%202022%3A%20the%20alleged%20gang%20leaders%20Ahmed%20%E2%80%98Gatu%E2%80%99%20Muaz%20and%20Ahmed%20%E2%80%98Ahandu%E2%80%99%20Ismail%20as%20well%20as%20the%20man%20seen%20following%20both%20Riz%20and%20Yameen%2C%20Ismail%20Abdul%20Raheem.%20At%20the%20time%20of%20writing%2C%20all%20are%20awaiting%20trial%20for%20acts%20of%20terrorism.%20DDCom%20alleged%20one%20of%20those%20involved%20in%20the%20murder%20had%20met%20with%20Raees%20Yameen%2C%20receiving%20assistance%20to%20join%20fellow%20suspects%20in%20Syria%20%E2%80%93%20a%20claim%20rejected%20by%20the%20former%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20225px)%2085vw%2C%20225px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F08144512%2Fdownload-8.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22225%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F08144512%2Fdownload-8.jpeg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F08144512%2Fdownload-8-150x150.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-672117%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22225%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDaniel%20Bosley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAttempts%20to%20break%20the%20cycles%20of%20failed%20justice%20resulted%20in%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Transitional%20Justice%20Act%20in%202020.%20With%20a%20remit%20to%20investigate%20everything%20from%20torture%20and%20the%20Maafushi%20prison%20shootings%20during%20Maumoon%E2%80%99s%20presidency%20to%20the%20Suvadive%20revolt%20and%20Amin%20Didi%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20the%20task%20of%20the%20new%20ombudsman%E2%80%99s%20office%20is%20vast%20in%20scope.%20With%20its%20term%20running%20only%20until%20the%20end%20of%20President%20Solih%E2%80%99s%20term%2C%20though%2C%20transitional%20justice%20could%20easily%20prove%20to%20be%20transitory%20once%20again.%20Stalled%20progress%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98Stealing%20Paradise%E2%80%99%20investigation%20is%20a%20continuous%20reminder%20that%20in%20small%20island%20societies%2C%20attempts%20to%20unravel%20such%20tangled%20webs%20are%20never%20simple.%20The%20historic%20corruption%20scandal%20has%20been%20predictably%20divisive%2C%20and%20the%20loudest%20critic%20of%20the%20Solih%20government%20is%20both%20surprising%20and%20unsurprising.%20From%20the%20moment%20the%202018%20election%20was%20won%2C%20it%20was%20obvious%20Nasheed%20would%20struggle%20to%20take%20a%20backseat%20role.%20Disagreements%20between%20the%20president%20and%20Speaker%20began%20almost%20immediately%2C%20barely%20slowed%20by%20the%206%20May%20attack.%20Soon%20after%20the%20blast%2C%20following%20the%20Speaker%E2%80%99s%20repeated%20threats%20to%20publicize%20details%20of%20the%20flagging%20investigation%2C%20a%20list%20of%20individuals%20allegedly%20involved%20was%20leaked.%20Those%20said%20to%20have%20benefitted%20from%20the%20scam%20included%20119%20people%20currently%20or%20formerly%20serving%20in%20government%20jobs%2C%20including%20sixteen%20sitting%20MPs%20(five%20from%20the%20MDP)%2C%20one%20former%20and%20one%20current%20cabinet%20minister%2C%20and%20a%20state%20minister.%20The%20latter%20two%20remained%20in%20their%20posts%2C%20because%20only%20former%20Raees%20Yameen%2C%20Adeeb%20and%20two%20others%20have%20been%20prosecuted%20at%20the%20time%20of%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EExcerpted%20with%20permission%20from%3C%2Fem%3E%20Descent%20into%20Paradise%3A%20A%20Journalist%E2%80%99s%20Memoir%20of%20the%20Untold%20Maldives%3Cem%3E%20by%20Daniel%20Bosley%2C%20published%20by%20Pan%20Macmillan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694166605000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F08133506%2Fimage-2021-12-08T133456.641.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhow-politics-came-full-circle-in-the-maldives%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Stalled%20progress%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98Stealing%20Paradise%E2%80%99%20investigation%20is%20a%20continuous%20reminder%20that%20in%20small%20island%20societies%2C%20attempts%20to%20unravel%20such%20tangled%20webs%20are%20never%20simple.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhow-politics-came-full-circle-in-the-maldives%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Natco%20Pharma%