C%20M.S.%20Subbalakshmi%20sat%20cross-legged%20on%20the%20floor%2C%20with%20her%20accompanying%20artistes%2C%20and%20became%20the%20first%20ambassador%20of%20Indian%20culture%20at%20the%20United%20Nations%20in%201966.%20Rendering%20mellifluously%20%3Cem%3EJagadodharana%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20raga%20kapi%2C%20MS%2C%20as%20she%20was%20famously%20known%2C%20received%20thundering%20ovation%20from%20a%20packed%20United%20Nations%20General%20Assembly%20audience.%20Her%20simplicity%2C%20her%20elegance%2C%20her%20voice%20and%20the%20sheer%20beauty%20of%20Purandhara%20Dasa%E2%80%99s%20composition%20placed%20Indian%20culture%20on%20the%20global%20map%2C%20just%20as%20Pandit%20Ravi%20Shankar%E2%80%99s%20sitar%20recital%20at%20Madison%20Square%20Garden%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20culture%2C%20high%20and%20popular%2C%20has%20much%20to%20offer%20that%20would%20stun%20global%20audiences.%20Time%20was%20when%20the%20Indian%20state%20understood%20how%20to%20present%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20great%20and%20diverse%20culture%20to%20a%20global%20audience%20%E2%80%93%20be%20it%20delegates%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20or%20young%20people%20at%20Madison%20Square%20Gardens.%20Something%2C%20however%2C%20has%20gone%20wrong.%20The%20official%20representation%20of%20Indian%20culture%20is%20becoming%20increasingly%20crass.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20laser%20lights%20stabbing%20the%20New%20Delhi%20sky%20out%20of%20Bharata%20Mandapam%2C%20the%20venue%20of%20the%20G20%20Summit%2C%20to%20the%20multi-coloured%20lighting%20of%20the%20Qutub%20Minar%2C%20kitsch%20has%20taken%20over%20from%20culture.%20Even%20Humayun%E2%80%99s%20Tomb%20has%20not%20been%20spared%2C%20with%20the%20dome%20above%20being%20used%20as%20white%20space%20for%20a%20G20%20logo%20to%20be%20projected%20on%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22In%20Photos%3A%20Life%20Behind%20the%20Curtain%2C%20or%20How%20Delhi's%20Poor%20See%20G20%20City%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2F