2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20real%20pleasure%20and%20honour%20for%20me%20to%20be%20together%20with%20my%20esteemed%20colleagues%20from%20all%20over%20all%20over%20the%20world%20at%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Farticle%2Fmedia%2Fm20-g20-media-freedom-press-news%3Futm%3Dauthorlistpage%5C%22%3EM20%20meeting%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20have%20been%20working%20as%20a%20journalist%20and%20I%20have%20been%20covering%20diplomacy%20and%20international%20affairs%20for%20various%20national%20and%20international%20media%20companies%20for%20more%20than%2025%20years%20now.%20I%20am%20also%20the%20vice-president%20of%20the%20International%20Press%20Institute%20Turkey%20National%20Committee%2C%20and%20a%20board%20member%20at%20the%20Turkish%20Journalist%20Union.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20would%20like%20to%20of%20course%20talk%20very%20briefly%20about%20the%20situation%20of%20media%20freedom%20in%20Turkey.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20situation%20of%20media%20freedom%20in%20Turkey%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20afraid%20what%20I%E2%80%99m%20about%20to%20tell%20you%20is%20not%20very%20bright%20and%20not%20very%20promising%20for%20the%20future%20of%20journalism%20and%20journalists%20in%20Turkey.%20My%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fm20-south-korea-prosecutor-fake-news%5C%22%3Ecolleague%20from%20South%20Korea%20said%20the%20media%20was%20very%20polarised%20in%20Korea%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20be%20honest%2C%20I%20would%20never%20think%20that%20I%20would%20miss%20those%20days%20when%20the%20media%20was%20polarised%20in%20Turkey%2C%20because%20polarisation%2C%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20means%20pluralism.%20However%2C%20right%20now%20more%20than%2090%25%20of%20the%20mainstream%20media%20in%20Turkey%20is%20either%20under%20the%20control%20of%20the%20government%2C%20or%20directly%20owned%20by%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20small%20scale%20independent%20websites%20and%20TV%20channels%2C%20and%20some%20small%20scale%20newspapers%20who%20are%20trying%20to%20survive%20with%20tight%20budgets%20and%20under%20harsh%20conditions%20in%20Turkey%2C%20but%20this%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20change%20the%20fact%20that%20more%20than%2090%25%20of%20the%20mainstream%20media%20is%20controlled%20by%20the%20government.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frsf.org%2Fen%2Fcountry-t%25C3%25BCrkiye%5C%22%3Elatest%20report%20of%20Reporters%20Without%20Borders%20(RSF)%2C%20Turkey%20is%20ranked%20165th%20out%20of%20180%3C%2Fa%3E%20countries%20in%20RSF%E2%80%99s%202023%20World%20Press%20Freedom%20Index%2C%20and%20according%20to%20the%20Turkish%20Journalist%20Union%20report%20on%20Freedom%20of%20Press%2C%20more%20than%2040%20journalists%20have%20been%20imprisoned%20in%20Turkey%20because%20of%20their%20journalistic%20activities%20over%20the%20past%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20very%20recently%2C%20a%20prominent%20investigative%20Turkish%20journalist%20Bar%C4%B1%C5%9F%20Pehlivan%2C%20whose%20latest%20book%20accused%20Turkey%E2%80%99s%20last%20interior%20minister%20of%20having%20links%20with%20organised%20crime%2C%20has%20been%20locked%20up%20for%20the%20fifth%20time%20in%20three%20years%3B%20having%20been%20jailed%2C%20released%20on%20parole%20and%20locked%20up%20again.%20This%20time%2C%20Bar%C4%B1%C5%9F%20Pehlivan%20has%20been%20ordered%20back%20behind%20bars%20by%20text%20message.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20report%20published%20by%20Germany%E2%80%99s%20Friedrich%20Naumann%20Foundation%20for%20Freedom%20in%202023%20says%20Turkey%20is%20unfortunately%20copying%20the%20Russian%20playbook%2C%20using%20the%20judiciary%20to%20silence%20critical%20journalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20the%20pressure%20and%20efforts%20of%20the%20government%20to%20take%20control%20of%20the%20media%2C%20journalists%20have%20been%20arrested%2C%20trailed%2C%20unemployed%20and%20forced%20to%20work%20with%20precarious%20unemployment%20and%20low%20wages%20for%20many%20years%20in%20Turkey.%20Although%20the%20number%20of%20journalists%20in%20prison%20has%20decreased%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20years%2C%20this%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20the%20pressure%20on%20journalists%20has%20decreased.%20While%20the%20pressures%20on%20the%20arrest%20of%20journalists%20have%20decreased%2C%20we%20observe%20that%20the%20pressures%20have%20increased%20through%20trials%20and%20fines.%20We%20have%20a%20public%20advertising%20agency%20in%20Turkey%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20sure%20you%20have%20similar%20establishments%20in%20your%20countries.%20This%20public%20advertising%20agency%20was%20founded%20to%20distribute%20public%20advertisements%20fairly.%20However%2C%20it%20has%20declared%20war%20on%20all%20newspapers%20criticising%20the%20government.%20Economic%20embargoes%20are%20imposed%20on%20newspapers%20by%20advertisement%20suspension%20sections.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20there%20is%20the%20Radio%20and%20Television%20Supreme%20Council%2C%20which%20is%20also%20an%20official%20institution%20in%20Turkey%2C%20and%20it%20has%20been%20imposing%20penalties%20amounting%20to%20millions%20of%20Turkish%20liras%20on%20independent%20television%20channels%20trying%20to%20bring%20the%20facts%20to%20the%20public%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20media%20group%20is%20of%20course%20pro-government%2C%20which%20is%20called%20Demir%C3%B6ren.%20They%20own%20the%20popular%20%3Cem%3EH%C3%BCrriyet%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EDaily%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EH%C3%BCrriyet%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20at%20which%20I%20used%20to%20work%20before%2C%20and%20poster%20newspapers.%20They%20also%20own%20the%20CNN%20T%C3%BCrk%2C%20the%20Turkish%20channel%20of%20CNN%2C%20and%20the%20Kanal%20D%20TV%20channel%2C%20and%20a%20number%20of%20other%20TV%20channels%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20would%20like%20to%20tell%20you%20very%20briefly%20about%20my%20personal%20story%2C%20because%20I%20believe%20it%20is%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20situation%20of%20journalism%20and%20journalists%20in%20Turkey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20work%20as%20the%20senior%20diplomatic%20correspondent%20for%20%3Cem%3EDaily%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EH%C3%BCrriyet%3C%2Fem%3E%20until%202020%2C%20when%20I%20was%20fired%20from%20the%20newspaper%20by%20the%20new%20pro-government%20owners%20of%20the%20newspaper%2C%20Demir%C3%B6ren.%20Until%20recently%2C%20%3Cem%3EH%C3%BCrriyet%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20the%20most%20major%20newspaper%20in%20Turkey%2C%20and%20it%20was%20called%20%E2%80%98The%20Admiral%20Ship%20of%20Turkish%20Media%E2%80%99.%20However%20in%20March%202018%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20%3Cem%3EH%C3%BCrriyet%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20used%20to%20be%20the%20Do%C4%9Fan%20Media%20Group%2C%20was%20forced%20to%20sell%20the%20newspaper%20and%20the%20whole%20media%20group%20to%20the%20pro-government%20businessman%2C%20Demir%C3%B6ren.%20If%20you%20wonder%20what%20Demir%C3%B6ren%20was%20doing%20before%2C%20the%20main%20business%20of%20Demir%C3%B6ren%20was%20selling%20bottled%20gas%20%E2%80%93%20which%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20media.%20So%20after%20Demir%C3%B6ren%20purchased%20%3Cem%3EH%C3%BCrriyet%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20journalists%20at%20the%20newspaper%2C%20including%20myself%2C%20started%20to%20get%20unionised%2C%20because%20we%20felt%20insecure.%20In%20September%202019%2C%20the%20number%20of%20journalists%20and%20other%20employees%20who%20had%20become%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Turkish%20Journalist%20Union%20had%20reached%20such%20a%20critical%20number%2C%20that%20the%20Turkish%20Journalist%20Union%20was%20almost%20going%20to%20get%20the%20authorisation%20in%20order%20to%20conduct%20a%20labour%20agreement%20with%20the%20employer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20before%20the%20union%20reached%20that%20critical%20number%2C%20%3Cem%3EH%C3%BCrriyet%3C%2Fem%3E%20laid%20off%2045%20journalists%20without%20any%20notice%20and%20without%20paying%20their%20legal%20compensation%20fees%2C%20because%20of%20their%20unionisation%20efforts.%20I%20am%20one%20of%20those%2045%20journalists%20who%20were%20laid%20off%20by%20sending%20legal%20notices%20to%20our%20homes.%20For%20instance%2C%20I%20learned%20that%20I%20was%20fired%20from%20my%20mother%20when%20I%20was%20at%20a%20news%20meeting%20at%20the%20office%2C%20because%20she%20was%20the%20one%20who%20received%20the%20legal%20notice%20at%20home%20which%20was%20sent%20by%20my%20employer.%20Plus%2C%20Demir%C3%B6ren%20has%20not%20paid%20our%20legal%20compensation%20fees%2C%20which%20was%20its%20legal%20obligation.%20The%2045%20journalists%20who%20lost%20their%20jobs%20have%20worked%20481%20years%20in%20total%20at%20H%C3%BCrriyet%2C%20and%20they%20got%20paid%20nothing%20for%20this.%20Of%20course%2C%20we%20have%20sued%20Demir%C3%B6ren%20in%20order%20to%20get%20our%20legal%20rights%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20too%20late%2C%20and%20the%20judiciary%20is%20unfortunately%20very%20slow%20in%20Turkey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20heard%20similar%20complaints%20from%20colleagues%20all%20over%20the%20world%20today.%20My%20colleague%20from%20Japan%2C%20Hiroki%20Sugita%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fjapan-china-press-m20%5C%22%3EMost%20of%20the%20young%20people%20don%E2%80%99t%20choose%20journalism%20as%20a%20profession%20anymore%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%20We%20have%20the%20same%20situation%20in%20Turkey%20%E2%80%93%20unfortunately%2C%20journalism%20is%20an%20erasing%20profession%20in%20Turkey%2C%20which%20is%20struggling%20to%20survive%20under%20difficult%20circumstances.%20So%20this%20is%20all%20I%20would%20like%20to%20tell%20you%20about%20the%20situation%20in%20Turkey%2C%20and%20about%20my%20personal%20story.%20I%20told%20my%20personal%20story%20just%20because%20I%20believe%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20situation%20of%20journalism%20in%20Turkey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20would%20like%20to%20thank%20you%20once%20more%20for%20organising%20this%20very%20important%20meeting%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20ready%20to%20take%20part%20in%20any%20future%20initiatives%20that%20can%20be%20formed%20after%20this%20meeting.%20Thank%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIpek%20Yezdani%20is%20an%20independent%20journalist%20and%20a%20former%20foreign%20editor%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3EH%C3%BCrriyet%3Cem%3E%2C%20Turkey.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694163039000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F08135629%2F14150056644_7ceafc3d0b_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fturkey-press-freedom-m20-demiroren%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Just%20very%20recently%2C%20a%20prominent%20investigative%20Turkish%20journalist%20Bar%C4%B1%C5%9F%20Pehlivan%2C%20whose%20latest%20book%20accused%20Turkey's%20last%20interior%20minister%20of%20having%20links%20with%20organised%20crime%2C%20has%20been%20locked%20up%20for%20the%20fifth%20time%20in%20three%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fturkey-press-freedom-m20-demiroren%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inside%20Pankaj%20Tripathi%E2%80%99s%20village-inspired%20home%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694162896000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103502016%2Cimgsize-17434.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fpankaj-tripathis-village-inspired-holiday-home-is-a-beautiful-refuge-from-the-hustle-and-bustle-of-mumbai%2Farticleshow%2F103501994.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103501994.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ENational%20Award-winning%20actor%20Pankaj%20Tripathi%20has%20created%20a%20village-inspired%20holiday%20home%20in%20Mumbai.%20Named%20'Roop%20Katha%2C'%20the%20home%20features%20scenic%20outdoors%2C%20mud%20stoves%2C%20clay%20pots%2C%20and%20more.%20Tripathi%20showcased%20th