tps%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fbox-office%2Fdream-girl-2-just-rs-4-crore-short-of-entering-the-100-crore-club%2Farticleshow%2F103500631.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103500631.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EWith%20the%20release%20of%20Jawan%2C%20Ayushmann%20Khurrana's%20Dream%20Girl%202%20seems%20to%20have%20hit%20a%20mountain%2C%20the%20film%20was%20able%20to%20make%20only%20one%20crore%20on%20Thursday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fbox-office%2Fdream-girl-2-just-rs-4-crore-short-of-entering-the-100-crore-club%2Farticleshow%2F103500631.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nepal-India%20Transit%20Trade%20Ties%20Can%20Unlock%20Economic%20Opportunities%2C%20Cross-Border%20Collaborations%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F29135107%2Findia-nepal-flags.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20June%201%2C%20Nepal%20renewed%20and%20revised%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fnepal-india-renew-transit-treaty-sign-deals-in-energy-connectivity%5C%22%3Eseven-year%20transit%20trade%20agreement%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20India.%20The%20updated%20treaty%2C%20signed%20in%20New%20Delhi%20by%20the%20prime%20ministers%20of%20both%20countries%2C%20enhances%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20access%20to%20designated%20Indian%20sea%20ports%20by%20road%2C%20rail%2C%20and%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20planned%20expansion%20of%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20petroleum%20import%20pipelines%20enhances%20supply%20chain%20security.%20Moreover%2C%20a%20long-term%20cross-border%20electricity%20trade%20agreement%20and%20a%20memorandum%20of%20understanding%20(MoU)%20on%20cross-border%20digital%20payments%20are%20seen%20to%20be%20breakthrough%20initiatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImproved%20access%20via%20land%20and%20water%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20transit%20agreement%20with%20India%20is%20crucial%20for%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20sea-borne%20trade%2C%20since%20ports%20in%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%20are%20much%20closer%20to%20Kathmandu%20(roughly%20900%20kilometres%20away)%20than%20to%20the%20nearest%20Chinese%20port%20of%20Tianjin%20(4000%20km%20away).%20Even%20for%20markets%20such%20as%20South%20Korea%2C%20accessible%20from%20the%20East%20China%20Sea%2C%20shipping%20by%20sea%20from%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%20would%20be%20more%20cost-effective%20than%20the%20combined%20land%20and%20sea%20route%20via%20China.%20In%20fact%2C%20using%20Bangladeshi%20ports%20makes%20more%20economic%20sense%20for%20Nepal%20for%20transit%20trade%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftepc.gov.np%2Fpages%2Ftrade-and-payment-agreement%5C%22%3Ea%20trade%20and%20transit%20agreement%20was%20signed%20in%201976%3C%2Fa%3E)%20than%20routing%20through%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20time%2C%20India%20has%20granted%20inland%20waterways%20access%20to%20Nepal%2C%20offering%20potential%20cost%20savings%20and%20congestion%20relief%20in%20the%20journey%20to%20Haldia%2FKolkata%20ports.%20There%20are%20also%20hopeful%20indications%20on%20access%20to%20two%20other%20ports%2C%20Dhamra%20and%20Mundra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIntegrated%20Check%20Posts%20(ICPs)%20streamline%20movement%20of%20goods%20and%20people%20across%20the%20borders.%20The%20two%20currently%20operational%20ICPs%20at%20Jogbani%20and%20Raxaul%2C%20handling%20the%20bulk%20of%20bilateral%20trade%2C%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flpai.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2022-07%2FTime_Release_%2520Study_LPAI.pdf%5C%22%3Elimited%20parking%20space%20and%20narrow%20access%20roads%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20constraining%20the%20daily%20crossing%20of%20as%20many%20as%20730%20trucks%20a%20day.%20To%20facilitate%20the%20growing%20volume%20of%20trade%2C%20a%20third%20ICP%20was%20inaugurated%20at%20the%20border%20of%20Nepalgunj%20(Nepal)%20and%20Rupaidiha%20(India)%2C%20and%20MOUs%20for%20two%20more%20ICPs%2C%20near%20the%20Nepalese%20towns%20of%20Bhairahawa%20and%20Dodhara%20Chandani%2C%20were%20signed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cross-border%20cargo%20rail%20link%20at%20the%20second-busiest%20Biratnagar-Jogbani%20border%20became%20operational%20with%20the%20first%20cargo%20train%E2%80%99s%20inaugural%20eight-kilometre%20run%20from%20Bathnaha%20in%20India%20to%20the%20Nepal%20customs%20yard.%20However%2C%20it%20stopped%20after%20the%20inaugural%20run%2C%20due%20to%20lack%20of%20coordination%20between%20the%20relevant%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20existing%20passenger%20rail%20link%20between%20Jaynagar%20(India)%20and%20Kurtha%20(Nepal)%20was%20extended%20by%2017%20km%20into%20Nepal.%20So%20now%20Nepal%20can%20deploy%20private%20rail%20operators%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENepal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Findia-positive-but-to-tread-cautiously-on-nepals-request-for-new-routes-to-save-its-airports-built-by-china-1224044.html%5C%22%3Ehas%20long%20requested%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20facilitate%20better%20international%20air%20connectivity.%20Its%20two%20new%20international%20airports%20in%20Pokhara%20and%20Lumbini%2C%20both%20located%20west%20of%20the%20existing%20Kathmandu%20airport%2C%20remain%20underutilised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20India%20only%20allows%20one%20air%20entry%20point%20for%20international%20flights%20into%20Nepal%2C%20flying%20over%20the%20Indian%20airspace%20via%20Simara%20(Nepal)%2C%20which%20is%20directly%20south%20of%20Kathmandu%2C%20on%20the%20Indian%20border.%20This%20puts%20international%20flights%20approaching%20Nepal%20from%20the%20west%20at%20a%20disadvantage%2C%20as%20they%20must%20make%20a%20detour%20through%20Simara.%20It%20also%20causes%20congestion%20at%20the%20Kathmandu%20airport.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENepal%20has%20been%20requesting%20for%20another%20entry%20point%20over%20the%20northwestern%20corner%20of%20Nepal%2C%20near%20Mahendranagar.%20However%2C%20India%20has%20expressed%20air%20safety%20concerns%20arising%20from%20potential%20multiple%20entry%20points%20on%20the%20Nepal-India%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20high%20altitude%20traffic%20is%20only%20allowed%20via%20Simara.%20This%20situation%20hinders%20the%20growth%20of%20international%20air%20traffic%20to%20Nepal%2C%20and%20a%20solution%20must%20be%20found%20by%20examining%20international%20experience%20in%20managing%20air%20corridors%2C%20while%20keeping%20in%20view%20India%E2%80%99s%20security%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPetroleum%20pipelines%20promote%20resilient%20and%20cost-effective%20supply%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENepal%20heavily%20relies%20on%20India%20for%20vital%20petroleum%20imports%2C%20which%2C%20until%202019%2C%20were%20transported%20via%20road.%20Occasional%20road%20disruptions%20in%20the%20past%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Freliefweb.int%2Freport%2Fnepal%2Fnepal-extreme-hardship-expected-worsen-food-prices-soar%5C%22%3Ehave%20caused%3C%2Fa%3E%20extreme%20hardship%20for%20Nepalis.%20To%20address%20this%20issue%20and%20ensure%20the%20avoidance%20of%20earlier%20hardships%2C%20India%20and%20Nepal%20have%20built%20a%2069-km%20pipeline%20from%20Motihari%20(India)%20to%20Amlekhgunj%20(Nepal).%20Since%202019%2C%20Nepal%20has%20been%20importing%20diesel%20through%20this%20pipeline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETransporting%20oil%20via%20pipelines%20is%20cost-effective%2C%20safer%2C%20minimises%20losses%2C%20and%20is%20not%20susceptible%20to%20road%20disruptions.%20In%20a%20bid%20to%20further%20reduce%20dependence%20on%20trucks%2C%20an%20MoU%20was%20signed%20during%20the%20prime%20ministers%E2%80%99%20meeting%20to%20extend%20the%20pipeline%20by%2062%20km%20to%20Chitwan%20in%20Nepal.%20Another%20MoU%20covers%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20new%2050-km%20pipeline%20from%20Siliguri%20(India)%20to%20Jhapa%20(Nepal)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBreakthrough%20long-term%20power%20trade%20agreement%20and%20a%20new%20tripartite%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20power%20trade%20with%20India%20involves%20both%20exports%20and%20imports.%20In%20the%20future%2C%20its%20power%20exports%20are%20likely%20to%20increase%20significantly%2C%20which%20requires%20supporting%20infrastructure%20as%20well%20as%20trading%20arrangements.%20Significant%20gains%20were%20made%20on%20both%20fronts%20during%20the%20Nepal%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENepal%20first%20achieved%20surplus%20power%20in%202021%2C%20but%20this%20is%20only%20the%20tip%20of%20the%20iceberg.%20Its%20hydroelectric%20power%20potential%20is%20enormous.%20However%2C%20finding%20a%20market%20for%20surplus%20power%20in%20from%20June%20to%20September%20is%20hard%2C%20even%20with%20an%20existing%20capacity%20of%20about%201200%20megawatts.%20That%20is%20only%20a%20fraction%20of%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adb.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fpublication%2F612641%2Fhydropower-development-economic-growth-nepal.pdf%5C%22%3Eeconomically%20viable%20potential%20of%2042%2C000%20MW%3C%2Fa%3E.%20With%20new%20capacity%20being%20added%2C%20and%20no%20storage%20possibility%2C%20the%20surplus%20generation%20problem%20in%20the%20wet%20months%20will%20only%20worsen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECross-border%20transmission%20lines%20are%2C%20therefore%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkathmandupost.com%2Fnational%2F2023%2F01%2F26%2Fnepal-to-propose-two-new-cross-border-transmission-lines-with-india%5C%22%3Ecritical%20for%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20electricity%20trade%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Most%20of%20the%2012%20existing%20transmission%20lines%20are%20low%20voltage%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmoewri.gov.np%2Fstorage%2Flisties%2FMay2020%2Fwhite-paper-2075-with-annex02.pdf%5C%22%3Ecannot%20carry%20much%20energy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20the%20400%20kV%20Gorakhpur-Butwal%20line%2C%20expected%20to%20be%20completed%20in%20the%20next%20two%20years%2C%20is%20significant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20transmission%2C%20India%20also%20signed%20a%20project%20development%20agreement%20for%20the%20Lower%20Arun%20hydroelectric%20project%20(669%20MW)%2C%20expected%20to%20take%20seven%20to%20eight%20years%20for%20its%20construction%20and%20an%20MoU%20for%20Phukot-Karnali%20hydroelectric%20project%20(480%20MW)%2C%20expected%20to%20take%20five%20years%20for%20its%C2%A0%20construction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20that%2C%20investors%20in%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20power%20sector%20need%20to%20be%20assured%20of%20demand%2C%20since%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20internal%20demand%20is%20only%20a%20fraction%20of%20its%20power%20generation%20potential.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20agreement%20to%20purchase%2010%2C000%20MW%20of%20power%20from%20Nepal%20over%20the%20next%20decade%2C%20doubling%20current%20annual%20purchases%20and%20transitioning%20away%20from%20yearly%20agreements%2C%20is%20a%20breakthrough.%20The%20agreement%20follows%20up%20on%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moewri.gov.np%2Fpages%2Fnotices%3Flan%3Den%26id%3D402%5C%22%3Ejoint%20vision%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20power%20sector%20cooperation.%20It%20will%20further%20enhance%20power%20exports%2C%20which%20already%20represent%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20third%20most%20important%20source%20of%20export%20revenue%2C%20totalling%20%2460%20million%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20Nepal%20trades%20part%20of%20its%20surplus%20power%20in%20bilateral%20mode%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iexindia.com%2F%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20Energy%20Exchange%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20specifically%20within%20the%20%E2%80%9CDay%20Ahead%20Market%2C%E2%80%9D%20where%20the%20market%20clearing%20price%20tends%20to%20rise%20during%20the%20monsoon%20months.%20Yet%2C%20in%20the%20dry%20season%2C%20the%20tables%20turn%2C%20and%20Nepal%20becomes%20an%20importer%20of%20power%20from%20India.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20fiscal%20year%202020-21%2C%20Nepal%20imported%20three%20times%20the%20amount%20of%20power%20it%20exported%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20caveat%20is%20that%20under%20the%20Indian%20regulations%2C%20plants%20with%20Chinese%20involvement%20will%20not%20qualify%20to%20export%20power%20to%20India%2C%20since%20India%20and%20China%20do%20not%20have%20a%20power%20trading%20agreement.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkathmandupost.com%2Fnational%2F2023%2F07%2F17%2Findia-puts-up-new-hurdle-to-importing-electricity-from-nepal%5C%22%3ESince%20signing%20the%20long-term%20agreement%2C%20India%20has%20initiated%20new%20financial%20scrutiny%20of%20plants%20selling%20power%20to%20India%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20major%20development%20is%20the%20entry%20of%20Bangladesh%20into%20the%20power%20trading%20equation.%20For%20the%20first%20time%2C%20transit%20trade%20in%20power%20will%20become%20a%20reality%20for%20Nepal%2C%20with%20India%20allowing%20its%20grid%20for%20export%20of%2040%20MW%20power%20from%20Nepal%20to%20Bangladesh.%20Though%20symbolic%2C%20this%20sets%20the%20stage%20for%20larger%20long-term%20power%20export%20from%20Nepal%20to%20Bangladesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20developments%20in%20cross-border%20power%20trade%20are%20a%20win-win%20for%20all%20countries%20involved.%20For%20Nepal%2C%20the%20gains%20are%20clear%2C%20as%20mentioned%20above.%20For%20India%2C%20the%20developments%20provide%20an%20equally%20important%20marker%20in%20its%20support%20for%20a%20bilateral%20and%20sub-regional%20energy%20market.%20By%20enabling%20cross-border%20energy%20export%20from%20Nepal%2C%20it%20is%20facilitating%20the%20long-desired%20development%20of%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20hydropower%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20enabling%20such%20trade%20to%20become%20trilateral%2C%20it%20is%20helping%20plant%20seeds%20for%20sub-regional%20energy%20cooperation.%20Finally%2C%20by%20promoting%20hydropower%20development%2C%20both%20from%20Nepal%20and%20Bhutan%2C%20India%20is%20supporting%20the%20transition%20to%20green%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20standpoint%2C%20the%20import%20of%20hydro-based%20electricity%20could%20serve%20as%20a%20crucial%20catalyst%20for%20reducing%20its%20heavy%20dependence%20on%20fossil%20fuels.%20The%20export%20of%2040%20MW%20of%20power%20from%20Nepal%20to%20Bangladesh%20could%20be%20just%20the%20beginning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Bangladesh%20and%20Nepal%20intend%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheannapurnaexpress.com%2Fnews%2Fnepal-bdesh-agree-on-sunkoshi-3-development-and-tripartite-energy-deal-with-india-42566%2F%5C%22%3Eto%20jointly%20develop%20the%20683%20MW%20Sunkoshi-3%20hydroelectric%20project%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20central%20Nepal%2C%20and%20export%20power%20to%20Bangladesh%20through%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPotentially%20transformative%20digital%20payments%20agreement%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENepal%20and%20India%20already%20allow%20Bank%20ATM%20debit%20cards%20and%20credit%20cards%20to%20be%20used%20across%20the%20border%20for%20withdrawing%20local%20currency%20and%20making%20point-of-sale%20transactions%20in%20local%20currency.%20Moreover%2C%20Nepali%20migrant%20workers%20in%20India%20use%20the%20Indo-Nepal%20Remittance%20Facility%20Scheme%20to%20remit%20money%20swiftly%20and%20cheaply%2C%20using%20Indian%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20MoU%20signed%20between%20Nepal%20and%20India%20on%20cross-border%20digital%20payments%20can%20be%20transformative.%20It%20is%20part%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20ongoing%20international%20expansion%20of%20its%20immensely%20successful%20Universal%20Payments%20Interface%20(UPI).%20Introduced%20in%202016%2C%20UPI-based%20real-time%20digital%20transactions%20accounted%20for%20three-fourths%20of%20all%20retail%20digital%20transactions%20in%20India%20in%20FY23.%20In%20Nepal%2C%20QR%20code-based%20point-of-sale%20transactions%20have%20climbed%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nrb.org.np%2Fcontents%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F2079_12_P-S-Indicators-of-Chaitra.pdf%5C%22%3Emonthly%20volume%20of%20nearly%208%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20mobile%2Fonline%20payments%20across%20banks%20are%20also%20rising.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20implemented%2C%20the%20MoU%20will%20ensure%20interoperability%20between%20the%20two%20countries%E2%80%99%20digital%20payment%20systems%2C%20promoting%20digital%20inclusion%2C%20minimal%20transaction%20costs%2C%20and%20convenience%2C%20enhancing%20person-to-person%20and%20person-to-merchant%20payments%2C%20and%20benefitting%20trade%20in%20goods%20and%20services%2C%20especially%20for%20a%20large%20number%20of%20cross-border%20travellers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConclusion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20details%20of%20the%20new%20transit%20treaty%20are%20not%20yet%20public%2C%20a%20reading%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F36643%2FVisit_of_Prime_Minister_of_Nepal_Rt_Honble_Mr_Pushpa_Kamal_Dahal_Prachanda_to_India%5C%22%3Eofficial%20press%20releases%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fin.nepalembassy.gov.np%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2FPress-Release-on-Rt.-Hon.-Prime-Ministers-Visit-to-India-.pdf%5C%22%3Etwo%20governments%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rooted%20in%20deeper%20economic%20engagement%2C%20have%20renewed%20optimism%20on%20bilateral%20trade%20and%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20transit%20trade.%20Along%20with%20breakthroughs%20in%20cross-border%20power%20trade%20and%20digital%20payments%2C%20these%20also%20augur%20well%20for%20the%20renewal%20of%20the%20vital%20Nepal-India%20trade%20agreement%20in%20November%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuccessful%20implementation%20of%20ongoing%20agreements%20can%20help%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20further%20deepening%20and%20broadening%20of%20economic%20ties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESanjay%20Kathuria%20is%20Visiting%20Senior%20Fellow%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20Social%20and%20Economic%20Progress%2C%20and%20Adjunct%20Professor%20at%20Georgetown%20and%20Ashoka%20Universities%2C%20and%20Global%20Fellow%20at%20the%20Wilson%20Center.%20He%20tweets%20%40Sanjay_1818.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3ET.G.%20Srinivasan%20is%20Visiting%20Senior%20Fellow%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20Social%20and%20Economic%20Progress.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20authors%20would%20like%20to%20thank%20Paras%20Kharel%20and%20his%20colleagues%20at%20SAWTEE%2C%20Nepal%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Uttam%20Malla%20(former%20DG%20of%20National%20Statistics%20Office%2C%20Nepal)%20for%20comments%20on%20an%20earlier%20version.%20Views%20are%20the%20authors%E2%80%99%20own.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694160621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F29135107%2Findia-nepal-flags.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fnepal-india-transit-trade-ties-can-unlock-economic-opportunities-cross-border-collaborations%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nepal%20and%20India%20have%20renewed%20their%20transit%20trade%20agreement%2C%20improving%20Nepal's%20access%20to%20Indian%20sea%20ports%20and%20inland%20waterways%2C%20boosting%20supply%20chain%20resilience.%20This%20also%20marks%20potential%20breakthroughs%20in%20cross-border%20electricity%20trade%20and%20digital%20payments.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fnepal-india-transit-trade-ties-can-unlock-economic-opportunities-cross-border-collaborations%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Man%20Arrested%20For%20Air%20Hostess'%20Murder%20Found%20Dead%20In%20Mumbai%20Police%20Custody%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%2040-year-old%20man%2C%20who%20was%20arrested%20for%20allegedly%20killing%2025-year-old%20air%20host